name: Chicken, You Can't Roost Too High for Me
Chicken Don't Roost Too High
comments: The Georgia Pot Lickers is the name that Lowe Stokes used for his lineup that recorded two sides for Okeh in Atlanta, Georgia on November 12, 1930. They consisted of Lowe Stokes (fiddle), Hoke Rice (guitar), and an unknown person on vocals using the "Dan Tucker" pseudonym. Stokes also recorded sides with Hoke Rice on November 10 and 11 under different "band" names.
